{"key":"processedPost-16062993","value":{"id":16062993,"first":16062078,"last":16067543,"when":1333942610,"utime":"04/09/12 06:36 AM","cleanedPost":"Acceptable for what?&nbsp; If you're making an outdoor bed, you want a combination of sawdust, chips and bark.&nbsp; If you're planning an indoor grow, mulch should be great.&nbsp; I grind all my chips into mulch with my shredder.&nbsp; Chips themselves tend to poke holes in the filter patch bags, so I quit using them at all for indoor grows.&nbsp; I only use sawdust and shredded bark.<br />Also, it doesn't have to be hardwood for most species.&nbsp; Well aged pine works, but be sure to spread the sawdust out in the sun for a full summer before use. I use Douglas fir sawdust/bark for our <a href=\"http://www.mushroomvideos.com/Mountain-Mushroom-Farm\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer noopener\">commercial shiitake farm</a>, not hardwood.<br />RR"}}